<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-12-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-24"><hi rend="italic">December 24,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Hill reports that the German foreign office telephones that it fully
                            agrees to the general principles laid down in Mr. Hitt’s memorandum
                            embodying telegram of November 6, and will reply in writing after
                            Christmas.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>